status: MARC21-007: Specific material designation of motion picture
Special class of motion picture to which the item belongs., e.g., a film reel.

definition (en): Encased in a cartridge that has the ends joined together to form a loop that provides playback without rewinding.
Encased in a cassette that winds and rewinds reel-to-reel.
A wound length of film not in a reel, cartridge, etc.
Open reel of motion picture film designed for use with a projector having its own take-up reel.
scope note (en): Includes sound track film intended to accompany visual images actually not present.

definition (en): Special material designation for the motion picture is not specified.
Specific material designation other than film cartridge, film cassette, film roll, film reel.
